body:
If a class member function has an input variable that is not consumed, and the compiler warnings are on (e.g. when developing Verilator), the compiler gives an error message.

Presumably we should suppress the warning, though I'd prefer to find a way to do this selectively so as to not mask real problems.

Blocks #1538 compile time

Found with UVM:

```
Vt_uvm_todo_uvm_pkg__03a__03auvm_reg_field__Vclpkg__DepSet_h44eb293d__0.cpp: In member function 'void Vt_uvm_todo_uvm_pkg__03a__03auvm_reg_field::__VnoInFunc_con$
Vt_uvm_todo_uvm_pkg__03a__03auvm_reg_field__Vclpkg__DepSet_h44eb293d__0.cpp:15:343: error: parameter 'is_rand' set but not used [-Werror=unused-but-set-parameter$
   15 | void Vt_uvm_todo_uvm_pkg__03a__03auvm_reg_field::__VnoInFunc_configure(VlProcessRef vlProcess, Vt_uvm_todo__Syms* __restrict vlSymsp, VlClassRef<Vt_uvm_t$
      |                                                                                                                                                          $
```

